  <description type="morphology">Herbs, often rather compact mats, 1–3.5 × 2–6 dm. Aerial flowering stems erect, 1–2(–3) dm, thinly floccose or glabrous, without one or more leaflike bracts ca. midlength. Leaves in loose rosettes; blade usually elliptic, 1–2 × 0.5–1.5 cm, glabrous on both surfaces (except in central Idaho, where sparsely floccose even at full maturity), margins plane. Inflorescences umbellate; branches 0.3–2(–2.5) cm, without a whorl of bracts ca. midlength; involucral tubes 1.8–3 mm, lobes 1–3 mm. Flowers 4–7 mm; perianth bright yellow.</description>
