  <discussion>Variety aureum is closely related to var. umbellatum, differing mainly in having glabrous leaf blades at full anthesis. However, var. aureum is much more widely distributed. At higher elevations, it is replaced by the weakly differentiated var. porteri. It is occasionally found in cultivation, especially in European gardens.</discussion>
